What is Execution Context in JavaScript?
An Execution Context (EC) is the environment in which JavaScript code is evaluated and executed.

Every time a script or function runs, a new execution context is created.

ğŸ”„ Types of Execution Context
Global Execution Context (GEC)

Created by default when the JS code starts running.

Creates the window object (in browser) or global object (in Node).

Binds this to global object.

Function Execution Context (FEC)

Created every time a function is called.

Has its own arguments, variables, and this.

Eval Execution Context (rare)

Created when eval() is used. Avoid using eval.

ğŸ§± Structure of Execution Context
Each EC has two phases:

ğŸ”¸ 1. Creation Phase
Memory is allocated.

Hoisting happens (variables and function declarations are stored in memory).

this is set.

Scope chain is established.

ğŸ”¸ 2. Execution Phase
Code runs line by line.

Variables are assigned values.

Functions are executed.

ğŸ” Example Breakdown:
javascript
Copy
Edit
var a = 2;

function foo() {
    var b = 3;
    return a + b;
}

foo();
ğŸ‘‡ What Happens Behind the Scenes:
ğŸ§  Global Execution Context (GEC)
ğŸŒ Creation Phase:
a â†’ undefined

foo â†’ reference to function

this â†’ window (in browser)

âš™ï¸ Execution Phase:
a = 2

foo() is called â†’ creates Function Execution Context

ğŸ§  Function Execution Context (FEC)
ğŸŒ Creation Phase:
b â†’ undefined

arguments â†’ {} (empty)

this â†’ window

âš™ï¸ Execution Phase:
b = 3

return a + b â†’ 2 + 3 = 5

ğŸ” Call Stack (Execution Stack)
JavaScript uses a Call Stack (LIFO) to manage execution contexts.

Example:
javascript
Copy
Edit
function one() {
  console.log("one");
  two();
}

function two() {
  console.log("two");
}

one();
Stack Behavior:
GEC pushed

one() â†’ FEC for one pushed

two() â†’ FEC for two pushed

console.log("two")

FEC for two popped

console.log("one")

FEC for one popped

GEC popped (end of script)

ğŸ”„ Hoisting in Creation Phase
javascript
